Defendant Dominick M Smith in court with attorney Victoria Mccandless.  Defendant Dominick M Smith in custody.  
James W. Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

AS TO COUNTS 1 AND 2:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 42 MONTHS EACH COUNT, CONSECUTIVE to each other and with any other sentence with credit for 0 days served. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 18 MONTHS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 24 MONTHS.

The defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.

BOTH COUNTS:  CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
*No alcohol or controlled substances (unless for mental health of physical treatment as prescribed by licensed physician);
*AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
*Urine screens- the Court recommends revocation upon any dirty urine analysis;
*Mental health assessment; treatment, if needed;
*Participate in Anger management counseling;
*Seek and maintain employment;
*Participate in job and vocational training;
*Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
* No contact with victims Raj S. and Vishai V.;
*Provide DNA sample if not previously done so- pay surcharge;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments,

The Court ordered restitution in the stipulated amount of $14,936.66 and $3835.26 to Crime Victim Compensation Program.  The Court ordered that all financial obligations and restitution be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.  Appeal rights given.
The Court orders defendant REMANDED into custody. 
